sed is for simple substitutions on individual lines, that is all. For anything other than s/old/new/ you should be using awk for simplicity, clarity, robustness, efficiency, portability and every other desirable attribute of software. Your requirements cannot be satisfied by simply s/old/new/ so therefore sed is not the right tool for this job. All sed constructs other than s, g, and p (with -n) are used today just for the mental exercise, not for production software as they became obsolete in the mid-1970s when awk was invented.

Better ways of looping are:
 `[1, 2, 3].forEach(function (el, index), { ... })` for Arrays
 `Object.keys().forEach(function (key) {... })` for the properties of an object. 
 `Array.prototype.forEach(document.links, function () { ...});` for Array-like objects like the HTMLCollection `document.links` returns.
